<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Example Pyramid Class Based Views Project</title>
    <meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html;charset=UTF-8"/>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="//netdna.bootstrapcdn.com/bootstrap/3.1.1/css/bootstrap.min.css"/>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-8 col-md-offset-2">
                <h1>Welcome to the Pyramid Views Example Project</h1>
                <p>
                    Pyramid Views gives you access to Django-style class-based
                    views from within Pyramid.
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="/about">About page</a> (simple <code>TemplateView</code> setup in <code>main()</code>)</li>
                    <li><a href="/book/list">Manage books</a> (<code>ListView</code>)</li>
                    <li><a href="/book/list">Create books</a> (<code>CreateView</code>)</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    There are currently <strong>${book_count} book(s)</strong> in the database.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
